Reasoning: The paper discusses the interference between filter bank (FB) based waveforms and legacy Cyclic Prefix-Orthogonal Frequency Division Multiplexing (CP-OFDM) in a coexistence scenario. This topic falls under the field of wireless communication and signal processing, which is covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as it deals with the study of communication systems and their limits. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as it covers the design and analysis of communication networks. cs.COMM (Computer Communications and Networks) is another possible category as it focuses on the design and analysis of communication protocols and systems. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category but still relevant as it covers the analysis and control of complex systems, which can include communication systems. Finally, cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category but still possible as it covers the processing and transmission of multimedia data, which can be affected by interference from coexisting communication systems.
